#X text 12 8 3 Introduction to Gem - Altering gem entities in 3D space
;
#X text 462 100 "rotateXYZ" accepts degrees of rotation (0-359). "scaleXYZ"
and "translateXYZ" \, on the other hand \, use gem units. Gem units
are arbitrary units that divide the gem space. The gem space for a
square gemwin is 8 units wide (x) \, 8 units tall (y) and 20 units
deep (z). The center of the gem space is at (0 \, 0 \, 0). (This is
the position in space on x \, y and z.) This means that in order to
put the entity in the upper left corner you need to send translateXYZ
(-4 \, 4 \, 0) (-4 for X \, 4 for Y \, and 0 for Z).;
